-- CTC Media 18 Years and Over Russian Audience Share Rises to 6.3%
-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 2012-04-05T15:47:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-05/ctc-media-18-years-and-over-russian-audience-share-rises-to-6-3-.html
CTC Media Inc. (CTCM) ’s average daily share
of viewers 18 years old and above rose to 6.3 percent in the
week to April 1, after falling the previous week, data compiled
by TNS-Global show.  Viewer share for CTC TV, the Nasdaq-listed Russian media
company’s biggest source of revenue, rose from 6.2 percent in
the week to March 25, data researcher TNS-Global said in an e-
mail today. CTC’s average daily audience among viewers four-
years-old and over remained unchanged at 7.4 percent in the week
to April 1, the data show.  NTV Television maintained the biggest average daily
audience share in Russia. NTV’s share of viewers 18-years-old
and over fell to 15.7 percent from 16 percent in the week to
March 25, while  Russia ’s Pervyi Kanal, which is controlled by
the government, had a 14.6 percent share, compared with 14.8
percent in the previous period. Rossiya-1 had 13 percent of
average daily share of viewers 18-years-old and over in the week
to March 25, from 12.8 percent in the previous week, TNS-Global
said. TNT had a 7.4 percent share, up from 7 percent.  NTV, Pervyi, Rossiya-1 and TNT were all ahead of CTC among
viewers ages 18 and over, TNS-Global said.  NTV’s share of viewers four-years-old and over dropped to
14.9 percent from 15.1 percent in the week to March 25. Pervyi
Kanal had a 14 percent share, from 14.2 percent in the previous
period. Rossiya-1 had 12.4 percent compared with 12.2 percent in
the previous week. TNT, with a 7.6 percent share, from 7.2
percent the week ended March 25, moved ahead of CTC as the
fourth-most watched television channel among viewers four-years-
old and over.  To contact the reporter on this story:
